<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">On June 23, 2022, Tesla, Inc. published the below pages on its website at <font style="text-decoration:underline;">www.tesla.com/2022shareholdermeeting</font> and <font style="text-decoration:underline;">www.tesla.com/2022-meeting-terms</font>:</p>
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU2"></a>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="ga0nrq1zinoz000001.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:621px;height:825px;"></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2020 Annual Meeting of Stockholders and Battery Day Tuesday, September 22, 2020 at 1:30 PM Pacific Time 2020 Annual Meeting of Stockholders and Battery Day Tuesday, September 22, 2020 at 1:30 PM Pacific Time Tesla&#8217;s&nbsp;&nbsp;2020&nbsp;&nbsp;Annual&nbsp;&nbsp;Meeting&nbsp;&nbsp;of&nbsp;&nbsp;Stockholders&nbsp;&nbsp;will&nbsp;&nbsp;be&nbsp;&nbsp;held&nbsp;&nbsp;on&nbsp;&nbsp;Tuesday,&nbsp;&nbsp;September&nbsp;&nbsp;22,&nbsp;&nbsp;2020,&nbsp;&nbsp;at&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;1:30&nbsp;&nbsp;PM&nbsp;&nbsp;Pacific&nbsp;&nbsp;Time.&nbsp;&nbsp;Immediately following&nbsp;&nbsp;the&nbsp;&nbsp;conclusion&nbsp;&nbsp;of&nbsp;&nbsp;the&nbsp;&nbsp;2020&nbsp;&nbsp;Annual&nbsp;&nbsp;Meeting,&nbsp;&nbsp;we&nbsp;&nbsp;will&nbsp;&nbsp;hold&nbsp;&nbsp;our&nbsp;&nbsp;separate Battery Day event.&nbsp;&nbsp;Live&nbsp;&nbsp;video&nbsp;&nbsp;webcasts&nbsp;&nbsp;of&nbsp;&nbsp;both&nbsp;&nbsp;events&nbsp;&nbsp;will&nbsp;&nbsp;be&nbsp;&nbsp;accessible to&nbsp;&nbsp;the general&nbsp;&nbsp;public&nbsp;&nbsp;below.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU3"></a>
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="ga0nrq1zinoz000002.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:597px;height:691px;"></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Livestream&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Virtual Meeting&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To accommodate ongoing public health requirements and travel considerations, we are also&nbsp;&nbsp;providing any stockholder as of July 31, 2020 the means to join the 2020 Annual Meeting&nbsp;&nbsp;virtually at www.meetingcenter.io/234436330. The virtual meeting will feature the same live&nbsp;&nbsp;video webcasts accessible to the general public above, plus the option to submit votes and&nbsp;&nbsp;written comments on meeting agenda items. In order to join the virtual meeting, you will&nbsp;&nbsp;need the password, which is tsla2020, and a 15-digit secure &#8220;control number&#8221; unique to you,&nbsp;&nbsp;which you may obtain as follows:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; If you are a &#8220;stockholder of record&#8221; with shares registered directly in your name with our&nbsp;&nbsp;transfer agent, Computershare Trust Company (a minority of Tesla stockholders), you can&nbsp;&nbsp;find the control number on the Notice of Internet Availability or paper proxy card that was&nbsp;&nbsp;sent to you (please check that it is for the meeting as scheduled for September 22, 2020,&nbsp;&nbsp;NOT as previously scheduled for July 7, 2020).&nbsp;&nbsp;If you are a &#8220;beneficial owner&#8221; and hold shares through a broker, bank or other&nbsp;&nbsp;organization (the vast majority of Tesla stockholders), you will have to register in advance&nbsp;&nbsp;to obtain a control number. Please ask your broker, bank or organization for a &#8220;legal&nbsp;&nbsp;proxy&#8221; for the 2020 Annual Meeting and submit a copy of it from your e-mail address with&nbsp;&nbsp;&#8220;Legal Proxy&#8221; in the subject line to legalproxy@computershare.com. If your request is&nbsp;&nbsp;received no later than 2:00 PM Pacific Time on September 17, 2020, you will receive a&nbsp;&nbsp;confirmation e-mail with your control number.&nbsp;&nbsp;Limited&nbsp;&nbsp;In-Person&nbsp;&nbsp;Events&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, we expect to accommodate a very limited number of stockholders in-person at&nbsp;&nbsp;the 2020 Annual Meeting and the Battery Day event due to mandated restrictions on the size&nbsp;&nbsp;of in-person gatherings. Both events will be held at:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="ga0nrq1zinoz000003.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:577px;height:852px;"></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tesla,&nbsp;&nbsp;Inc.&nbsp;&nbsp;901&nbsp;&nbsp;Page A Fremont,&nbsp;&nbsp;CA&nbsp;&nbsp;94538&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We are excited&nbsp;&nbsp;to&nbsp;&nbsp;be able to&nbsp;&nbsp;host&nbsp;&nbsp;attendees&nbsp;&nbsp;in&nbsp;&nbsp;Terms&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;1.&nbsp;&nbsp;Participation. Tesla will conduct a random drawing to determine its stockholders&#8217; eligibility&nbsp;&nbsp;to attend its 2020 Annual Meeting and separate Battery Day event in person. The drawing will&nbsp;&nbsp;be held strictly in accordance with these 2020 Annual Meeting &amp; Battery Day Drawing Terms&nbsp;&nbsp;(&#8220;Terms&#8221;), and no exceptions will be made. Participation is voluntary and does not create a&nbsp;&nbsp;legal partnership, agency, or other relationship between an applicant and Tesla. Entries must&nbsp;&nbsp;be made by Friday, August 28, 2020 at 11:59 PM Pacific Time. Incomplete applications or&nbsp;&nbsp;attempted applications by means other than through the online application form will not be&nbsp;&nbsp;considered.&nbsp;&nbsp;NO PURCHASE OR PAYMENT OF ANY KIND IS NECESSARY TO APPLY OR BE SELECTED. A&nbsp;&nbsp;PURCHASE OR PAYMENT WILL NOT INCREASE AN APPLICANT&#8217;S CHANCES OF BEING&nbsp;&nbsp;SELECTED. DRAWING IS VOID WHERE PROHIBITED BY APPLICABLE LAW.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;By participating in the drawing, each applicant certifies that such applicant is of the legal age&nbsp;&nbsp;of majority in the jurisdiction in which such applicant resides (at least 18 years of age in many&nbsp;&nbsp;countries) and such applicant represents that such applicant is a stockholder and is legally&nbsp;&nbsp;permitted to participate.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2.&nbsp;&nbsp;Eligibility. Each applicant will be required to submit proper evidence of stock ownership as&nbsp;&nbsp;of July 31, 2020, which must be one of the following and must show the name of the&nbsp;&nbsp;stockholder:&nbsp;&nbsp;For &#8220;stockholders of record&#8221; on July 31, 2020,&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a &#8220;Notice of Internet Availability&#8221; or paper proxy card that was sent to the stockholder&nbsp;&nbsp;(please check that it is for the meeting as scheduled for September 22, 2020, NOT as&nbsp;&nbsp;previously scheduled for July 7, 2020); or&nbsp;&nbsp;a statement of ownership from Tesla&#8217;s transfer agent, Computershare, confirming stock&nbsp;&nbsp;ownership as of July 31, 2020.&nbsp;&nbsp;For &#8220;beneficial owners&#8221; on July 31, 2020,</p>
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="ga0nrq1zinoz000004.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:624px;height:777px;"></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">a notice regarding the 2020 Annual Meeting received from the broker, bank or other&nbsp;&nbsp;organization through which shares were held (please check that it is for the meeting as&nbsp;&nbsp;scheduled for September 22, 2020, NOT as previously scheduled for July 7, 2020); or&nbsp;&nbsp;a &#8220;legal proxy&#8221; document from such organization indicating the stockholder&#8217;s authority to&nbsp;&nbsp;vote the shares at the 2020 Annual Meeting (please check that it is for the meeting as&nbsp;&nbsp;scheduled for September 22, 2020, NOT as previously scheduled for July 7, 2020); or&nbsp;&nbsp;a statement or letter from such organization confirming stock ownership as of July 31,&nbsp;&nbsp;2020.&nbsp;&nbsp;If selected, an applicant will be asked to submit a copy of valid government-issued&nbsp;&nbsp;identification and, where applicable, proof of address for such applicant. If the applicant is the&nbsp;&nbsp;stockholder and is a natural person, the name shown on such identification must match the&nbsp;&nbsp;name shown on the submitted evidence of stock ownership, as well as the name on the&nbsp;&nbsp;application. If the applicant represents a stockholder that is an entity, such applicant will also&nbsp;&nbsp;be asked to submit acceptable evidence of such applicant&#8217;s legal ability to represent the&nbsp;&nbsp;stockholder, which must match the name shown on such identification. Acceptable&nbsp;&nbsp;government-issuedidentification must, at a minimum, include the applicant&#8217;s current photo, full&nbsp;&nbsp;name, address or place of birth, identification number, and date of birth. If a selected applicant&nbsp;&nbsp;cannot satisfy these requirements in a timely manner, the selection will be forfeited.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;THERE IS A MAXIMUM OF ONE APPLICATION PER STOCKHOLDER. TESLA WILL SCREEN&nbsp;&nbsp;FOR MULTIPLE APPLICATIONS BY OR ON BEHALF OF THE SAME STOCKHOLDER&nbsp;&nbsp;(INCLUDING REPRESENTATIVES OF THE SAME STOCKHOLDER ENTITY), AND ALL&nbsp;&nbsp;IDENTIFIED MULTIPLE APPLICATIONS BY OR ON BEHALF OF A STOCKHOLDER WILL BE&nbsp;&nbsp;DISQUALIFIED.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;3.&nbsp;&nbsp;Guests. Each application is personal to the applicant submitting it. If an applicant is&nbsp;&nbsp;selected, under no circumstances will a spouse, domestic partner, child, or other family&nbsp;&nbsp;member or guest of such applicant (including a joint owner of shares) be admitted to the&nbsp;&nbsp;events unless such other person has separately applied for the drawing in his or her capacity&nbsp;&nbsp;as a stockholder and been selected. If the stockholder is an entity, only its legal representative&nbsp;&nbsp;who applies for and is selected in the drawing will be eligible for admission.&nbsp;&nbsp;4.&nbsp;&nbsp;General Conditions. All determinations by Tesla with respect to the drawing or any&nbsp;&nbsp;applicant&#8217;s eligibility will be final. Tesla, in its sole discretion, will determine the validity of each&nbsp;&nbsp;application. If Tesla determines or believes that any application is fraudulent, illegitimate or&nbsp;&nbsp;invalid, or that any applicant has failed to comply with or has violated any provision of these&nbsp;&nbsp;Terms, Tesla will have the right in its discretion to disqualify any affected applicant(s).&nbsp;&nbsp;Tesla reserves the right to modify these procedures or whether and how the in-person portion&nbsp;&nbsp;of the events will be held in its sole discretion. Tesla may be required to or choose to further&nbsp;&nbsp;change the date, time, location and/or format of the events. Irrespective of changes in&nbsp;&nbsp;schedule, government travel restrictions or other foreseeable and unforeseeable events,&nbsp;&nbsp;Tesla will not be responsible for any travel or lodging arrangements made or other expenses&nbsp;&nbsp;incurred in anticipation or furtherance of attending the events in person.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU4"></a>
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="ga0nrq1zinoz000005.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:624px;height:787px;"></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">INVITATIONS TO ATTEND THE EVENTS ARE NOT TRANSFERABLE AND ANY ATTEMPT TO&nbsp;&nbsp;TRANSFER AN INVITATION TO ANY OTHER PERSON WILL BE VOID AND WILL RESULT IN&nbsp;&nbsp;SUCH INVITATION BEING RESCINDED.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;5.&nbsp;&nbsp;Release and Limitations. By participating in this drawing, and to the extent there are any&nbsp;&nbsp;media recordings (photograph/video) of the event, each applicant authorizes and releases&nbsp;&nbsp;Tesla, or its respective licensees, affiliates, successors, and assignees the right, where&nbsp;&nbsp;permitted by law, without any further notice, review or consent to print, publish, broadcast,&nbsp;&nbsp;distribute, and use, worldwide in any media now known or hereafter in perpetuity and on a&nbsp;&nbsp;worldwide basis, the photographs, images or video shared or captured with or on behalf of&nbsp;&nbsp;Tesla, including, without limitation, the content of media including subjects captured,&nbsp;&nbsp;associated content, voice, likeness, image or statements, as well as metadata information for&nbsp;&nbsp;any purpose including but not limited to news, publicity, advertising, public relations, or other&nbsp;&nbsp;promotional purposes without any expectation of compensation or remuneration now or in the&nbsp;&nbsp;future.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each applicant also agrees that Tesla will have no liability for, and shall be held harmless by&nbsp;&nbsp;such applicant against, any liability for any injuries, losses or damages of any kind to persons,&nbsp;&nbsp;including personal injury or death, or property resulting in whole or in part, directly or&nbsp;&nbsp;indirectly, from acceptance, or participation in this drawing, or any claims based on publicity&nbsp;&nbsp;rights, defamation or invasion of privacy. The released parties are not responsible if any&nbsp;&nbsp;eligibility is revoked due to cancellations, delays, or interruptions due to acts of God, acts of&nbsp;&nbsp;war, natural disasters, weather, or terrorism.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6.&nbsp;&nbsp;Notification of Selection. Each selected applicant will be notified by direct email using the&nbsp;&nbsp;email address provided during the application. Each selected applicant must respond to the&nbsp;&nbsp;direct email message within forty-eight (48) hours after the direct email message is sent. If&nbsp;&nbsp;such selected applicant does not respond to the direct email message with a submission of&nbsp;&nbsp;legible and complete copy of any additional proper evidence demonstrating eligibility to&nbsp;&nbsp;attend this event as described in Section 2, such selected applicant may be disqualified, and&nbsp;&nbsp;Tesla reserves the right to select an alternative applicant at random.&nbsp;&nbsp;7.&nbsp;&nbsp;Conduct. By participating in this drawing, each applicant agrees in advance, if selected, to&nbsp;&nbsp;conduct himself or herself at the events in a responsible, professional and courteous manner,&nbsp;&nbsp;free from disruptive behavior, including foul language and obscene gestures (as well as any&nbsp;&nbsp;obscene or indecent messages on signs or clothing). Each selected applicant will further&nbsp;&nbsp;comply with local California public health authority requirements, requests from Tesla staff&nbsp;&nbsp;regarding safety and any changes to operations and/or emergency response procedures. Any&nbsp;&nbsp;lack of adherence to this code of conduct may result in permanent disqualification from future&nbsp;&nbsp;Tesla events, as well as potential violation of local ordinances resulting in possible arrest and&nbsp;&nbsp;prosecution.&nbsp;&nbsp;8.&nbsp;&nbsp;Governing Law. Any litigation or dispute resolution between the applicant and Tesla arising&nbsp;&nbsp;out of or relating to these Terms, will take place in the Northern District of California, and each&nbsp;&nbsp;applicant and Tesla hereby consent to the personal jurisdiction of and exclusive venue in the&nbsp;&nbsp;state and federal courts within that District with respect to any such litigation or dispute&nbsp;&nbsp;resolution. This Agreement will be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU5"></a>
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="ga0nrq1zinoz000006.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:624px;height:788px;"></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> the United States and the State of California, except that body of California law concerning&nbsp;&nbsp;conflicts of law.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;9.&nbsp;&nbsp;Privacy. Each applicant applying for a chance to attend the events in-person acknowledges&nbsp;&nbsp;and understands that the application information submitted may be stored and processed in&nbsp;&nbsp;any country which Tesla has facilities or in which Tesla engages service providers. Those&nbsp;&nbsp;countries may not have the same data protection laws as the country in which an applicant&nbsp;&nbsp;initially provided that information. When Tesla transfers information from or about an applicant&nbsp;&nbsp;to other countries, Tesla will protect it as described in Tesla's Privacy Notice. By submitting&nbsp;&nbsp;your application, or otherwise providing information to Tesla, each applicant consents to the&nbsp;&nbsp;transfer of information from or about such applicant to countries outside of such applicant&#8217;s&nbsp;&nbsp;country of residence, including the United States. Applicant information will not be used for&nbsp;&nbsp;marketing, and processed and retained only for the purposes described herein, and in&nbsp;&nbsp;accordance with Tesla's Privacy Notice.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
